<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1436,1188,1385]" pageId="0" pageNumber="599">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1258,1281]" pageId="0" pageNumber="599">Etymology:</emphasis>
A combination of the surname Ripley and the Greek ὄρνις (Ornis), a bird, and a common suffix for bird genera. This name honors S. Dillon Ripley, former Secretary of the Smithsonian Institution, for his extensive work on the birds of 
<collectingCountry box="[240,295,1328,1351]" name="India" pageId="0" pageNumber="599">India</collectingCountry>
and southern Asia. Gender masculine.
</paragraph>
